# Fluff Date: 2026-02-12 20:24:28
overview:<p>The Enfield is a fifty-ton medium BattleMech whose origins trace back to the Star League era, originally conceived as an urban combat platform to replace the aging Wyvern. Though the design never reached mass production before the fall of the Star League, its plans survived hidden among the engineering archives on Achernar, where Federated Suns soldiers discovered them in 2870. The Federated Suns kept knowledge of the design classified for nearly two centuries, lacking the technological base to produce its advanced components. It was not until the early 3050s that the New Avalon Institute of Science selected the Enfield as a companion design to the popular Enforcer, and in 3055 Blackstone BattleMechs, Ltd. on Inarcs began full production. The Enfield has since become closely associated with Lyran and Federated units deployed along the Clan border, filling a close-fire support role in medium and heavy lances.</p>

capabilities:<p>The Enfield is built on a Blackstone MD2E endo steel chassis and powered by a Magna 250 XL engine, granting it a respectable top speed of eighty-six kilometers per hour while freeing considerable tonnage for weaponry and protection. Eleven tons of StarGuard III armor with CASE provide solid protection for a design of its weight class, and the ammunition feed is shielded against catastrophic detonation. The reliance on an extra-light engine, however, has earned the Enfield an undeserved reputation for fragility, as the loss of either side torso will disable the 'Mech entirely.</p><p>The primary armament centers on a Defiance Disintegrator LB 10-X autocannon capable of firing both solid and cluster munitions, making the Enfield effective against both ground targets and aerospace assets. A Thunderbolt-12 large pulse laser mounted on the opposing arm delivers accurate close-range firepower, and the combination of cluster rounds and pulse laser fire can exploit breaches in enemy armor with devastating effect. Supporting weapons include a pair of Defiance B3M medium lasers and a ChisComp 32 small laser for close-quarters engagements. Eleven double heat sinks manage the thermal load effectively, keeping the Enfield cool under most combat conditions. The design's primary weakness is its lack of jump jets, which limits its effectiveness in broken or urban terrain and forces it to rely on lancemates to prevent flanking maneuvers.</p>

deployment:<p>The END-6Q is the base production model of the Enfield as manufactured by Blackstone BattleMechs beginning in 3055. Mounting the full complement of an LB 10-X autocannon, large pulse laser, two medium lasers, and a small laser, the 6Q represents the design as originally envisioned by Star League engineers and refined by the NAIS. It was deployed primarily to Lyran Alliance units along the Clan border and to Federated Commonwealth-employed mercenary commands. Despite solid firepower and adequate speed, its extra-light engine proved a liability in sustained engagements, leading to the development of more survivable variants.</p>

history:<p>The Enfield's history is one of long dormancy followed by a troubled introduction. The original Star League-era design was intended to serve as a medium urban combat 'Mech, but it never progressed beyond planning before the Amaris Civil War and the subsequent Succession Wars buried it among countless other lost technologies. The rediscovery of the plans on Achernar in 2870 gave the Federated Suns a potential edge, but lacking the industrial capacity to produce endo steel, extra-light engines, and LB-X autocannons, the design remained shelved for generations.</p><p>The technological renaissance spurred by the recovery of the Helm Memory Core and the shock of the Clan Invasion finally made production feasible. The NAIS refined the design in the early 3050s, making aesthetic and loadout adjustments to ensure compatibility with the Enforcer in combined-arms lances. Blackstone BattleMechs, Ltd., a relatively new manufacturer that had formed its BattleMech division in 3053, secured the production license and delivered the first Enfields in July 3055. Blackstone's close relationship with the Blackstone Highlanders mercenary unit provided a ready pool of field testers, and the Highlanders would eventually field the largest concentration of Enfields outside the regular armed forces.</p><p>Initial deployment prioritized units along the Clan border, but the Lyran Alliance's secession from the Federated Commonwealth complicated distribution. Ironically, very few Enfields reached Davion units as intended, with the bulk going to Lyran loyalist commands. Those Davion units that did receive the design paired it with Enforcers as originally planned, and the combination proved effective in evaluation exercises. In actual combat, however, the Enfield's performance was considered mediocre. The extra-light engine made it vulnerable to the kind of concentrated fire common in heavy engagements against Clan and Inner Sphere opponents alike, and commanders frequently reported Enfields returning from battle crippled or not at all.</p><p>During the FedCom Civil War, elements of the Seventh Crucis Lancers inflicted serious damage on Blackstone's production lines on Inarcs in 3065, halting full production until late 3066. The Jihad saw the factory survive intact, though industry-wide disruptions affected output. Commanders increasingly held Enfields in reserve during the heaviest fighting, deploying them as fire support behind sturdier lancemates rather than committing them to the front line. After the Jihad, many commands quietly transferred their Enfields to reservist and militia formations in favor of more survivable medium designs, though the type continued to serve in second-line and garrison roles.</p><p>Separately, during the Golden Century, Clan Mongoose produced its own version of the Enfield at the Cudahy Assembly Plant Delta on Circe, upgrading the design with prototype Clan weaponry. Following the Absorption of Clan Mongoose by Clan Smoke Jaguar, the fate of this line remains unclear, though the facility later produced other designs under Jaguar and subsequent Clan ownership.</p>

